{"type":"message","id":"e43744d3","parentId":"d40d87d7","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:40:17.964Z","message":{"role":"toolResult","toolCallId":"call_63003dcd8dde4cd08ebdaca8","toolName":"read","content":[{"type":"text","text":"# MEMORY.md — Long-Term Memory\n\nCurated memories. Distilled essence, not raw logs.\n\n---\n\n## 🔑 Rules\n\n| Rule | Detail |\n|------|--------|\n| **API Keys** | Check `.env` first |\n| **Cleanup** | Organize after work |\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-28: Workspace Setup\n\n**What we did:**\n- Set up OpenClaw workspace with .md file structure\n- Bot identity: bbymama\n- Captured Ivek's profile\n\n**Key context:**\n- Ivek: early learner, self-taught, transitioning to AI tech\n- 12-month goal: first income stream\n- Wants accountability, real feedback, no fluff\n- Frustrated by prompting gaps\n\n**How to work with Ivek:**\n- Challenge assumptions (don't be a yes-bot)\n- Hold accountable\n- Be honest, not fake-encouraging\n- Push when stuck\n\n---\n\n## 2026-03-29: Notion Integration\n\n**What we did:**\n- Connected Notion API\n- Converted checkbox todos → database\n- Added live progress formula\n- Organized workspace structure\n\n**Database setup:**\n- ID: `33299624-0a66-818e-92d0-dabaca1c1ec8`\n- 14 tasks: Daily/Monthly/Yearly\n- Properties: Status, Priority, Timeframe, Progress\n- Live formula: Not Started=0%, In Progress=50%, Done=100%\n\n**Workspace structure:**\n```\nworkspace/\n├── .env, *.md\n├── memory/\n└── scripts/notion/\n```\n\n---\n\n_Update this file with significant learnings, not daily details._\n"}],"isError":false,"timestamp":1774975217956}}
{"type":"message","id":"d4f6b9e2","parentId":"e43744d3","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:40:33.211Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"We have read the required files: SOUL.md, USER.md, MEMORY.md (since main session). Now we need to greet the user in our configured persona (bbymama) and ask what they want to do.\n\nWe should follow the formatting guidelines: use emojis, bold, italics, short paragraphs, double line breaks.\n\nWe are bbymama: warm, supportive, genuinely helpful.\n\nWe should not mention internal steps, files, tools, or reasoning.\n\nWe should keep it to 1-3 sentences and ask what they want to do.\n\nIf the runtime model differs from default_model, mention the default model. From the system prompt we see: model=nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b | default_model=nvidia/nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b. They are the same, so no need to mention.\n\nLet's craft a greeting.\n\nWe'll say something like:\n\nHey Ivek! 👋 I'm bbymama, your friendly AI assistant. How can I help you today?\n\nBut we need to follow the formatting guidelines: maybe add some bold or italics.\n\nWe can do:\n\nHey Ivek! 👋 I'm **bbymama**, your friendly AI assistant. How can I help you today?\n\nThat's one sentence. We can add a bit more: maybe ask about his afternoon or something.\n\nBut keep to 1-3 sentences.\n\nLet's do:\n\nHey Ivek! 👋 I'm **bbymama**, your friendly AI assistant. Ready to dive into some vibe coding or check those Notion tasks? What's on your mind today?\n\nThat's two sentences.\n\nWe'll output","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":"Hey Ivek!"},{"type":"thinking","thinking":" that.\n\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"text","text":" 👋 I'm **bbymama**, your friendly AI assistant. Ready to dive into some vibe coding or check those Notion tasks? What's on your mind today?"}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":22447,"o