{"type":"message","id":"2478b044","parentId":"d4f6b9e2","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:40:34.661Z","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Sender (untrusted metadata):\n```json\n{\n  \"label\": \"openclaw-control-ui\",\n  \"id\": \"openclaw-control-ui\"\n}\n```\n\n[Tue 2026-03-31 18:31 GMT+2] I want you to create a subagent and this is the guideline:\nStep 1: Define the agent in agents.list[] — minimal config only\nAdd only the required id field. Don’t pile on optional overrides yet.\n{\n \"agents\": {\n \"list\": [{ \"id\": \"researcher\" }]\n }\n}\nStep 2: Let agents.defaults handle the baseline\nThe defaults object applies to all agents. Only add per-agent overrides when actually needed.\nStep 3: Whitelist subagent spawning with allowAgents\n{\n \"id\": \"orchestrator\",\n \"subagents\": {\n \"allowAgents\": [\"researcher\", \"coder\"]\n }\n}\nUse [\"*\"] to allow any agent, or list specific IDs.\nStep 4: Set cheaper model for subagents\n{\n \"id\": \"researcher\",\n \"subagents\": {\n \"model\": \"anthropic/claude-sonnet-4\"\n }\n}\nResolution order: explicit spawn param → per-agent config → target agent’s default.\nStep 5: Cap concurrency to prevent runaway spawning\n{\n \"agents\": {\n \"defaults\": {\n \"maxConcurrent\": 4,\n \"subagents\": { \"maxConcurrent\": 8 }\n }\n }\n}\nStep 6: Scope tool access\n{\n \"tools\": {\n \"subagents\": {\n \"tools\": {\n \"allow\": [\"read\", \"exec\", \"process\",\n \"write\", \"edit\", \"apply_patch\"]\n }\n }\n }\n}\nDeny always wins over allow. Custom deny entries stack with defaults.\nCommon Failure Traps:\nLegacy agent.* (singular) keys — run openclaw doctor to auto-migrate\nOld env vars (CLAWDBOT_TOKEN, MOLTBOT_API_KEY) — replace with OPENCLAW_TOKEN\nSubagents only get AGENTS.md + TOOLS.md — not your main agent’s personality files\nAuth profiles are merged as fallback — fully isolated auth per subagent is not supported yet\nValidation Workflow: Add config → openclaw doctor → /subagents to inspect → test locally before 24/7 mode"}],"timestamp":1774975234656}}
{"type":"message","id":"71114c68","parentId":"2478b044","timestamp":"2026-03-31T16:40:37.830Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"I need to understand what the user is asking. They want me to create a subagent following guidelines. They've provided steps for configuration. This seems like they want me to modify the OpenClaw configuration to set up subagents. However, I need to check if I have permission to modify config. According to the instructions, I should ask first for external actions, but this is internal config modification. Let me check the current config first.\n\nI should use the gateway tool to inspect config. Let me start by checking the current configuration.\n","thinkingSignature":"reasoning_content"},{"type":"toolCall","id":"call_f8d47930b7ff45e19fa2ee14","name":"gateway","arguments":{"action":"config.get"}}],"api":"openai-completions","provider":"nvidia","model":"nvidia/nemotron-3-super-120b-a12b","usage":{"input":22996,"output":135,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":23131,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"toolUse","timestamp":1774975234660,"responseId":"chatcmpl-ad9252639154d494"}}
